cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with generating new clothing on a wearer through generative adversarial learning, which involves image synthesis and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new approach for generative modeling, which involves the use of a compositional mapping layer, and a spatial constraint to guide the generation of a semantic segmentation map. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper uses the DeepFashion dataset and conducts a user study, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
